 even without any new idea they continued to move through the countryside pitching the tent in a different place each night for security every morning they made sure that they had removed all clues to their presence then set off to find another lonely and secluded spot traveling by apparition to more woods to the shadowy crevices of cliffs to purple moors mountainsides and once a sheltered and pebbly cove every twelve hours or so they passed the horcrux between them as though they were playing some perverse game of where they dreaded the music stopping because the reward was twelve hours of increased fear and anxiety 
 
